# Code Style

Vite + React 19 + React Router. No Next.js App Router. React Compiler, `ref`, and package manager rules: **[CURSOR.md](../../CURSOR.md)**.

## TypeScript

### `type` vs `interface`

- **Props, object shapes** that may be extended â†’ **`interface`**
- **Unions, mapped/utility types, aliases** â†’ **`type`**

```ts
// Good
interface ButtonProps extends React.ComponentProps<"button"> {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
}

type Status = "DRAFT" | "PUBLISHED";

// Bad â€” Props as a loose type alias when an interface would do
type ButtonProps = { variant?: string };
```

### Type-only imports

Use **`import type`** for type-only symbols when applicable (**`verbatimModuleSyntax`** is on in `tsconfig.base.json`).

### Exports

- Prefer **named exports** for shared UI, feature modules, hooks, and utilities.
- **`src/pages/*.tsx`**: **default export** is allowed and matches the current route pattern (`routes/index.tsx` imports page components).
- Avoid default exports elsewhere unless there is a strong reason (e.g. a single-function module). New **`components/ui`**, **`features/*`**, and **`lib/*`** code should use named exports.

```ts
// components/ui/Button.tsx â€” prefer
export { Button, buttonVariants, type ButtonProps };

// pages/HomePage.tsx â€” OK
export default function HomePage() {
  /* ... */
}
```

## Imports

### Path alias

Use the **`@/`** alias for everything under `src/`. Avoid deep relative imports (`../..`) for app code.

```ts
// Good
import { cn } from "@/lib/cn";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui";

// Bad
import { cn } from "../../lib/cn";
```

### Order (logical)

Prettier does not enforce import groups in this repo. Suggested order:

1. `react`, `react-dom`, `react-router` (and other externals)
2. **Blank line**
3. **Internal** `@/...`
4. **`import type`** blocks may stay last or immediately after value imports from the same module â€” keep consistent within a file.

Run **`pnpm format`** before PRs.

## Naming

| Item | Rule | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| React component | PascalCase | `Button`, `BoardList` |
| Hook | camelCase, `use` prefix | `useAuthStore` (store), `useMediaQuery` |
| Utility | camelCase | `cn`, `formatDate` |
| Constant | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_FILE_SIZE` |
| Type / interface | PascalCase | `ButtonProps`, `AuthState` |
| SVG as component (SVGR) | PascalCase + `Icon` suffix | `ArrowRightIcon` |
| Zustand store hook | `use{Name}Store` | `useAuthStore` (see `src/stores/authStore.ts`) |

## File naming

| Kind | Rule | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| Component | PascalCase `.tsx` | `Button.tsx`, `BoardList.tsx` |
| Page (route screen) | PascalCase `.tsx` + default export OK | `MainPage.tsx` |
| Hook | camelCase `.ts` | `useMediaQuery.ts` |
| Store | camelCase `.ts` | `authStore.ts` |
| Utility / lib | camelCase `.ts` | `cn.ts` |
| Route config | camelCase `.tsx` / `.ts` | `index.tsx` under `routes/` |

Feature code lives under **`src/features/{feature}/`**; shared UI under **`src/components/ui/`** â€” see **[architecture.mdc](./architecture.mdc)**.

## Tailwind CSS

- Merge classes with **`cn()`** from **`@/lib/cn`** (Tailwind merge + `clsx`). Avoid string templates for conditional classes when `cn` can express it.

```tsx
// Good
<div className={cn("text-text-normal", isActive && "bg-brand-primary-light", className)} />

// Avoid when cn is clearer
<div className={`text-text-normal ${isActive ? "bg-brand-primary-light" : ""}`} />
```

- **`prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` is not installed** â€” class order is not auto-sorted. Keep groups readable (layout â†’ spacing â†’ typography â†’ colors â†’ state) or add the plugin later if the team wants enforced order.

